Date of Birth: September 18, 1848<br/>
Birthplace: Carbunca, Iowa, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: October 27, 1880<br/>
Death: October 13, 1911<br/>
<br/>
Born Sept. 18, 1848, at Carbunca (now part of Council Bluffs), Pottawattamie Co., Iowa, to George Albert Smith and Sarah Ann Libby. ,
Ordained apostle Oct. 27, 1880, by, Wilford Woodruff, at age 32;
sustained as second counselor to President Joseph F. Smith April 7, 1910, at age 61;
died Oct. 13, 1911, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at 63.